    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Asymptomatic at birth because of adequate systemic perfusion through a PDA and initially high pulmonary vascular resistance\nAs the PDA begins to close and pulmonary vascular resistance decreases, may develop:\nHypotension\nAcidosis\nRespiratory distress\nSymptoms can rapidly progress from cyanosis, increased respiratory distress, and poor feeding to\nheart failure\nand\ncardiogenic shock",
