    "Management": {
      "text": "Stabilize cardiopulmonary function prior to surgery\nMaintain PDA to provide sufficient mixing of oxygenated and deoxygenated blood, and adequate systemic perfusion\nProstaglandin E1\nStart infusion at 0.05 mcg/kg/min IV and titrate up to 0.1 mcg/kg/min, monitoring for hypotension and apnea\nSide Effects: Hypotension, Bradycardia, Seizures and Apnea\nStaged surgical repair\nFirst stage (Norwood procedure) performed in neonates\nSpO2 ranges in mid 70s-80s\nSecond stage (bidirectional Glenn procedure) performed at 3-6 months\nSpO2 ranges in mid 70s-80s\nThird stage (Fontan procedure) performed at 18-30 months\nPreload dependent with SpO2 ranging from low to high 90s",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Prostaglandin E1",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Prostaglandin_E1"
        }
      ]
    },
